  "texts": [
    "The ATAC AUROC is used to measure the alignment of different modalities in the ATAC feature space.",
    "It has been previously used to evaluate the quality of ATAC predictions 65.",
    "For each method to be evaluated, we first use it to convert different modality combinations that do not contain ATAC into ATAC features, respectively, calculate the AUROC of each converted result by taking the true ATAC features as the ground truth and finally take the average of these AUROCs as the final score.",
    "Taking MIDAS as an example, if ATAC, RNA and ADT data are involved, the evaluation is based on the combinations {RNA}, {ADT} and {RNA, ADT}.",
    "For each combination, we feed the data into the trained model to generate the imputed data of all modalities {ATAC, RNA, ADT} (see, 'Imputation for missing modalities and features'), where the generated ATAC features are used for AUROC calculation."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}